name: Sparks vs Fever
summary: Caitlin Clark, one of the most promising young stars in the WNBA, returns to action when her Indiana Fever host the Los Angeles Sparks on Wednesday, September 4th. The game will be televised on CBS Sports and Prime Video, and tip-off is scheduled for 7:00 PM ET. The Fever are currently riding a two-game winning streak and will be looking to continue their momentum against a Sparks team that has lost four of its last five games. Clark has been a bright spot for the Fever this season, averaging 18.7 points, 7.3 rebounds, and 7.6 assists per game. She is a dynamic scorer and playmaker who can impact the game in a variety of ways. Bettors are keeping a close eye on Clark's three-point shooting prop, as she is one of the most prolific three-point shooters in the league. The Sparks will be a tough opponent for the Fever, but they will be short-handed without starting point guard Brittney Sykes. The Fever will need to take advantage of Sykes' absence and make life difficult for Sparks star Nneka Ogwumike.

name: Joker 2
summary: "Joker: Folie à Deux" has garnered a range of reactions from critics, with some praising the performances of Joaquin Phoenix and Lady Gaga, while others criticize the film's musical elements and overall execution. TheWrap lauds Phoenix's "daring" performance, while The Hollywood Reporter highlights the chemistry between Phoenix and Gaga. Deadline focuses on the film's musical aspect, while The Guardian expresses disappointment with the "spiraling out of tune" musical sequel. Variety describes Phoenix and Gaga as "a cracked musical," and CinemaBlend finds the sequel both provocative and thought-provoking. IndieWire suggests the musical elements may be intentionally bad, and Forbes provides a summary of both positive and negative reviews. NME praises Gaga's performance in a "provocative prison musical," and The Independent finds the film as "bleak and daring" as the original.
